node.text:
This is @realjeremysuarez who pretty much became the second star of the show! I relate to this quite a lot. I went through the same thing and it’s very common in this industry to go from having tons of money rolling in to trying to figure out how to pay your bills and book your next gig. It’s especially hard when you’ve gone from being on a popular TV show to having to audition again and reintroduce yourself to casting. When you’re a child and trying to process life it can be exceptionally hard and challenging on your esteem. The decision to stop with this “up in the air” kind of career and do something more stable is a VERY hard one and there is no right answer. It’s a lot of people saying “weren’t you” and “what happened to” or “why are u here??” because they don’t see this industry as it is. They see the glitz and glamour, they don’t know that many of us child entertainers were taking care of our whole families and when we got to that awkward stage of rebuilding our careers many doors were shut. So it’s like saying “why don’t you have a job anymore” and many of us didn’t know why whatever was working “stopped.”

I remember when my mom asked after TJVP if I wanted to go to college or grind my nose to the ground and start over as an adult in this business.. I said I would rather continue to preform because it’s all I’ve known and it’s all I have ever loved. I owe it to many of you that watched me produce my own content and supported me as I evolved into who I am at this stage. When I started to create my own stuff I started to feel a lot more free. I would and have done it for free, that’s how much it’s always meant to me so I followed my heart and let God lead the way. 

That was what was best for ME, but Jeremy I respect you so much for doing what was right for you and you speaking your truth makes me feel so seen! It’s important we share and normalize this industry outside of the eye catching things people recognize it for. I can’t wait until we get our opportunity to work together! I always wanted to as kids, let’s make it happen as adults ♥️🙏🏾

node.text:
Soooo excited to share with you guys my newest investment with @glosslab! 

Not only do we have these on the go kits (that you see me using in the car here lol) but we also have standing locations in NY 😍 — but that’s not the best part, the gaggg is you can get an unlimited monthly membership! Meaning, when we are running late, left our kit at home and need to stop, with your #Glosslab membership you can get your nails done right then and there and you don’t have to worry about anything unsanitary! Everything is completely fresh person to person! Also, did I mention it’s an UNLIMITED MEMBERSHIP?? That means something to me. I always need my damn nails done hahaha 

I couldn’t be happier to be backing this company, especially post covid when it’s become a little harder to just enjoy a mani and pedi without the paranoia of what is gonna get you out there. I’m a hygiene freak and if you are as well, #Glosslab is for you! 

Check out the link in my story!!

#BigBoss #InvestingHottie #LookGreat #FeelGreat #DoGreat💅🏾😅♍️🙏🏾❤️‍🔥

node.text:
I had a really good weekend.

Life is overwhelming and also beautiful. I’m quite the workaholic but I am making time to have fun and be with friends in the midst of it all. I miss New York a lot but being back in LA reminds me of my teenage years and how hard things were to balance between career and regular life. It’s good for me to see how that has changed. I’m a work in progress, sis got big dreams!!!

I’m just really happy you guys. Love u!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by BIG BOSS 🔑🔑 on July 13, 2021. May be an image of 5 people and text that says 'വരയ Television Academy EMMYS Outstanding Actress InA Short Form Comedy Or Drama Series 2021 KEKE PALMER TURNT UP WITH THE TAYLORS'.

node.text:
I can’t say how thankful I am to my team @lukecdillon, Dave Becky, @maxwyeth, @shayladavis135!!!! Of course @facebookwatch and @thekidsatplay for allowing #TurntUpWithTheTaylors to happen!! It’s one thing to live your dreams and get a chance to make people laugh and just playyyy. It’s another to be acknowledged for it even in the smallest way!

This is my life’s work and there is more comedy to come. Thank you @televisionacad for this nomination!!!! ♥️🙏🏾😩🙌🏾
